A task requiring determining the final positions of a set of objects given their initial positions and a description of a sequence of swaps.

Q: Alice, Bob, and Claire are playing a game. At the start of the game, they are each holding a ball: Alice has a yellow ball, Bob has a blue ball, and Claire has a pink ball.
As the game progresses, pairs of players trade balls. First, Claire and Alice swap balls. Then, Alice and Bob swap balls. Finally, Claire and Bob swap balls. At the end of the game, Bob has the
Options:
(A) yellow ball
(B) blue ball
(C) pink ball
A: (A)

A: (C)

Q: In a game of musical chairs, five people - Alice, Bob, Claire, Dave, and Eve - are sitting around a table with five chairs. The game starts with each person sitting in a chair: Alice is in chair 1, Bob is in chair 2, Claire is in chair 3, Dave is in chair 4, and Eve is in chair 5.
As the game begins, the people start to get up and move around. First, Claire and Dave get up and move to the other side of the table, so that Claire is now in chair 4 and Dave is in chair 3. Then, Bob and Alice get up and move to the other side of the table, so that Bob is now in chair 1 and Alice is in chair 2. Finally, Eve and Claire get up and move to the other side of the table, so that Eve is now in chair 3 and Claire is in chair 4. In the end, the person sitting in chair 1 is
Options:
(A) Alice
(B) Bob
(C) Claire
(D) Dave
(E) Eve
A: (B)||
